Colombia Stocks: ETB, Ecopetrol Decline; Cementos Argos Rises

-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 
2011-04-11T20:56:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-11/colombia-stocks-etb-ecopetrol-decline-cementos-argos-rises.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index fell 0.5 percent to 14,482.01, while the
Colcap Index dropped 0.3 percent to 1,703.10.  Empresa de Telecomunicaciones de Bogota SA  (ETB CB), the
state-run phone company serving  Colombia ’s capital, fell 3.9
percent to 612 pesos. Comptroller Monica Certain gave the
company 10 days to file a plan of action to keep from continuing
to lose value after failing to find a strategic partner to
finance an expansion,  Caracol Radio  reported on its website
April 9.  Cementos Argos (CEMARGOS CB) rose 1 percent to 10,600
pesos. The company announced today completion of a 900 billion
peso ($495 million) roadway in Barranquilla, according to the
daily La Republica.  Ecopetrol SA (ECOPETL)  , Colombia’s largest oil company,
dropped 1.7 percent to 3,700 pesos, its lowest price since Sept.
30, 2010, as crude fell from a 30-month high after the
 International Monetary Fund  cut its growth forecasts for the
U.S. and  Japan .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blake Schmidt in Bogota at 
 Bschmidt16@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
